metadata.name: The Arcimboldo Project #43
metadata.description:
A tribute to Giuseppe Arcimboldo (1526 - 1593), an Italian painter best known for creating imaginative portrait heads made entirely of objects such as fruits, vegetables and flowers.

This token is made of a combination of 192 layers (24 layers x 8 fruits/vegetables/flowers categories).
All the layers have been hand-painted in acrylics on paper and digitally composed.
The background has a random HSV color.

As always a big thank you goes to Koei Ural - @KoeiUral for the huge help with the p5.js code!

metadata.name: Dencity #9
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: 7 Years of Bad Luck #303
metadata.description:
## Flavor text 
Supposedly it all started with the Romans. When breaking a mirror your soul would be cursed. Fortunately, the Romans also believed that the soul renews every 7 years. So actually, breaking a mirror brings you at most 7 years of bad luck, but I supposed the "at most" part was dropped because it didn't sound as cool.

## The Algorithm
The mirror shards are created by recursively breaking up a base shape into smaller pieces. Once the mirror is broken each shard is displaced. This is not a packing algorithm.

The texture is created using domain warped Perlin noise.

## Main Features
- 26 color palettes.
- 3 types shape groups (square, 5-10-sided-polygon, circle).
- 4 levels of 'brokenness' -- the number of mirror shards.
- 2 methods for breaking up the shards.

metadata.name: Artifice #302
metadata.description:
This series is is about playful obfuscation.

The fxtext article linked on the main profect goes more in-depth into what is meant by that, as well as the events that led to this collection.

5640 bytes of Vanilla JS with no libraries. Palettes make up a third of the code.

In live mode:
‘S’ : save as png (3000 × 3600)
’V’ : save as svg (without grain)

URL params in live mode:
‘g=n’ : no grain
‘g=p’ : paper grain
‘h=t’ : high resolution mode, 9000 ×10600 (Chrome only, and may take a moment)

For example, if you wanted paper grain in high resolution, append “&g=p&h=t” to the url in live mode.

After rendering with these params, tapping 'P' will then save a png with those settings applied.

metadata.name: Quantum Fortresses #2
metadata.description:
Enter the world of Quantum Fortresses, where each NFT is a masterful blend of art and algorithm. This generative art collection on fxhash showcases fortresses that are not just built—they’re born from a complex interplay of 50 distinct layers, each contributing to the unique identity of every piece.

In Quantum Fortresses, the layers are carefully crafted to offer a rich diversity of elements, ensuring that no two fortresses are alike. These 50 layers include a mix of structural components, background elements, dynamic noise patterns, and glowing orbs, all of which come together to create a fortress that is both visually striking and full of character.

Key Layers:

Foundations: Solid bases that set the stage for the fortress, ranging from stone platforms to floating islands.
Walls and Towers: Varied in style and texture, these layers include towering spires, crenellated walls, and defensive structures.
Gates and Windows: Decorative and functional elements that add depth and detail, from ornate archways to glowing windows.
Background Landscapes: Evolving noise patterns that shift from misty mountains to abstract digital terrains.
Orbs of Power: Glowing, mystical spheres that interact with the environment, varying in color, size, and energy levels.

With these 50 possible layers, the combinations are virtually limitless, resulting in an expansive collection of fortresses that each tell their own story. Whether you discover a fortress bathed in the glow of a cosmic storm or a stronghold surrounded by swirling digital noise, each NFT in Quantum Fortresses is a unique, algorithmically crafted masterpiece waiting to be collected.

Dive into Quantum Fortresses and explore the intricate layers of this generative world, where every NFT is a gateway to a new digital dimension.

metadata.name: Warzone Selfies #51
metadata.description:
"Warzone Selfies" is a groundbreaking NFT collection that reimagines superheroes in the most unexpected and ironic of settings—war zones. Each piece in this collection captures a different iconic superhero, poised with a selfie stick amidst the chaos and destruction of conflict. The bright, bold aesthetics of superhero culture clash with the grim reality of war, creating a powerful commentary on the absurdity of our times.

These NFTs are more than just digital art; they are a statement on the modern obsession with self-image and social media, where even the world's mightiest heroes can't resist capturing their own moment of fame, no matter how inappropriate the setting. Each artwork in the collection is a unique, generative creation, combining elements of pop culture, dark humor, and social critique to make a lasting impact on viewers.

metadata.name: Oceans Pop Voyage: Portal 888 #3
metadata.description:
Within the vibrant expanse of "Oceans Pop Voyage: Portal 888," each collected NFT is a unique portal into the depths of creativity, blending the dynamic energy of pop art with the serene beauty of the ocean. As part of a limited series of 1,000 tokens, each NFT is a distinct masterpiece, capturing the essence of a journey through a world where the sea's vastness meets the bold, vivid strokes of pop art.

Every NFT in this collection is a fragment of the ocean’s story, reimagined through a kaleidoscope of colors and forms. From the undulating waves to the intricate coral structures, each piece resonates with the rhythm of the ocean, yet pulsates with the unmistakable flair of pop art. The collected NFTs together form a mosaic of this underwater voyage, where each token is a key to exploring the endless possibilities within this artistic fusion.

Owning an NFT from "Oceans Pop Voyage: Portal 888" means possessing a piece of this imaginative seascape, a vibrant relic of an artistic journey that celebrates both the timeless allure of the ocean and the electric energy of pop culture. Whether displayed individually or as part of a larger collection, these NFTs are tokens of an extraordinary voyage, each carrying the unique signature of this underwater, pop-inspired adventure.

metadata.name: Polako #27
metadata.description:
"Polako" means "slowly" in Montenegrin. When I first came here, the word I heard most often when I wanted to do something with someone or ask them for something was "Polako." In the culture I grew up in, everything happened very quickly and was results-oriented. In my new city, it's the opposite. Things may move slowly, requiring patience, but the aim is for better results. Perhaps they're right; the longevity of quickly done things is debatable. Our contemporary culture is like that too, everything is based on consumption. Art fields are also affected by this trend. Many artists or works without a past become popular with instant attention and then disappear after a while. This is sad in the long run. But when artists who don't get the recognition they deserve face these situations, they question themselves and their art, feeling inadequate and unsuccessful. As someone who has experienced this a lot, I am a keen observer. But speed is not necessary. What's important is to be lasting. Yes, this is very difficult. It's really hard to endure life and make your production sustainable. I must be patient. I need to mature my ideas. Slower, more polako. Surely, our art will be appreciated. There is a hidden connection between slowness and faith.

In this collection, I have returned to my architectural world once again. I have designed new compositions for depth. I moved away from colors and focused on textures. I tried to draw attention to changing animations in the background and spontaneously formed pixel layouts in the foreground.

*Start and stop animation: press 'Q'
*Save image: press 'W' to save the current image as a PNG.
*Fullscreen mode: press 'E'

metadata.name: Quantum Vacuum #315
metadata.description:
Empty space is not empty. It's filled with energy, transient fluctuations in quantum fields, bubbling with virtual particles popping in and out of existence. 

Part of an ongoing series of work combining my fascination with the fringes of fundamental physics, the emergence of complex behaviour through the interaction of very simple rules, and my obsession with hacking our perceptual systems. 

/Disclaimer: This is not a simulation, but an artistic conceptual interpretation and dramatization. :)
